# API Conventions

- Use Fastify route handlers with typed request/reply via `@bdaily/shared` schemas.
- Validate all inputs with Zod schemas defined in `packages/shared`.
- Services are classes injected into routes — never put business logic directly in route handlers.
- Error handling: throw `AppError` subclasses (NotFoundError, UnauthorizedError, ValidationError) which the global error handler maps to HTTP status codes.

## File Organization

- `src/routes/` — route definitions (thin, delegate to services)
- `src/services/` — business logic classes
- `src/services/ticket-system/` — strategy interface + implementations
- `src/middleware/` — auth, error handling, logging
- `src/db/` — Prisma client and schema

## Examples

```typescript
// Route handler — thin, delegates to service
app.get('/daily/:date', { preHandler: [authenticate] }, async (req, reply) => {
  const report = await dailyService.getByDate(req.user.id, req.params.date);
  return reply.send({ data: report });
});
```
